		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="28" desc="">
		<original>
			Infant baptism:
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="29" desc="">
		<original>
			A baby cannot have faith, and since we are baptized through faith in the power of God (Colossians 2:12), babies cannot be baptized. Original sin: Ezekiel 18:20 teaches that there is no original sin; each person is responsible for his own actions and will be judged accordingly. Therefore babies are born sinless and will be saved if they die.
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/colossians-2-12.html">
			<original>
				Colossians 2:12
			</original>
			<translated>
				
			</translated>
		</change>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/ezekiel-18-20.html">
