			</original>
			<translated>
				
			</translated>
		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="32" desc="">
		<original>
			"Baptism is a work — yet we are saved by faith:"
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="33" desc="">
		<original>
			(Ephesians 2:8): Colossians 2:11-15 teaches that we are saved by faith — in the working of God at baptism (v.12). This passage also teaches that circumcision as an eight-day-old baby under the old covenant has its spiritual parallel in the new covenant to baptism, as this is the time that Christ cuts away your old life. At baptism one enters a "covenant" with God — salvation.
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/ephesians-2-8.html">
			<original>
				Ephesians 2:8
			</original>
			<translated>
				
			</translated>
		</change>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/colossians-2-11-15.html">
