		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="36" desc="">
		<original>
			"Baptism isn't important. After all, look at what Paul said about it in 1 Corinthians 1:17:"
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/1-corinthians-1-17.html">
			<original>
				1 Corinthians 1:17
			</original>
			<translated>
				
			</translated>
		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="37" desc="">
		<original>
			Paul does not diminish the importance of baptism here. (Paul himself was baptized to have his sins forgiven in Acts 22:16.) In context (read 1 Corinthians 1:10-17), he makes the point that he does not want people following men (denominationalism). He mentions baptism several times in the passage.
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" href="scriptures/acts-22-16.html">
			<original>
				Acts 22:16
			</original>
