		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="38" desc="">
		<original>
			"The thief on the cross was not baptized and Jesus told him that they would see each other in paradise:"
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="39" desc="">
		<original>
			Jesus had not even died yet, and baptism is participating in his death (Romans 6:2-4); also on earth, he had the power to forgive sins (Matthew 9:2-6).
		</original>
		<translated>
			
